Ok, first, I never claimed the spell setup was logical, what I did claim is that there are some things the just arent worth arguing about, because nothing will change them.  <br>
<br>
By weird cryptic analogies Im guessig you mean the preacher alcholoic one.  My knowledge of the history of statistics is not good enough to include a date, but my analgoy refers to a study done, if I had to guess I believe somewhere around WW1, that showed that the more preachers there were in a town the more alcoholics there were.  <br>
<br>
What the study didnt show is that there were more preachers in the town simply because town a was bigger than town b.  In other words more preachers didnt cause more alcoholics, both were products of larger populations.  But the study didnt mention that the towns with more preachers were bigger, and almost everyone who reads it the first time tries to figure out how preachers cause alcoholism.  This study was never truly serious, I will point out, it was more of a learning exercise, but it was meant to demonstrate that you cant argue preachers cause alcoholism without more backround info.  <br>
<br>
Which in turn is the same as me trying to explain that you cant argue more dd damage by class A means better dd damage by class A than B, because class B might be able to cast twice as fast for 75% the damage of a single nuke of class A.  Yes Im sorry my last example was horribly cryptic, if anyone didnt understand it tell me, Ill try to explain better, but teaching has never been my strong suit.<br>
<br>
