Huh? No really, most of the issues he brings up I (and I hope others) do see his point, just they are not worth having verant change these things, its only worth mentioning them to rally players to our cause, or some such idealic nonsense as that.  <br>
<br>
&gt;&gt;Cazic Gate is fine with levitate on and they did move the drop spot from the left side to the center of the pad. Porting in without aggro is easy now.&lt;&lt;<br>
<br>
What does levitate do for aggro? And I could swear they never moved the tp spot, but whatever.<br>
<br>
&gt;&gt;Concussion is 39 because of channeling purposes to make it actually useful, not because the quest is intended for lower levels. If they make it higher level it will fizzle as bad as Atol's or Shield of the Magi, making it worthless until about 59/60. Don't have them mess up a spell that is actually useful and works.&lt;&lt;<br>
<br>
Ok from my, admitedly limited, understanding of channeling, channeling works solely based on your channel skill, not on the level of the spell plus channel.  And the stuff about fizzling is exaclty what Grim is saying people are wrong about, so do you know differently? Do you have proof?  <br>
<br>
&gt;&gt;We are still needed more than ever (pending the lurefix in the next patch) post 50. Enough already.&lt;&lt;<br>
<br>
Please at least finish the thought.  From my experience up to 51, that should read We are still needed more than ever post 50 for raids and events, but exp groups scoff at us as inefficient.<br>
<br>
&gt;&gt;Gaze/Glimpse/etc do work exactly like a telescope spell, it would be too much work to make something that actually increases your clippane. &lt;&lt;<br>
<br>
Or they could figure out where you would be, using glimpse, to get that same view, put a non aggro, non visible (as in no graphics), level 1 eye of zomm in that place instead.  The effect would be pretty much the same, but now you would get a new place to start the clip plane from where this little creature is.<br>
